<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Says Krajina Cease-Fire `Encouraging Step' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kinkel Says Krajina Cease-Fire `Encouraging Step' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3103151194 Hamburg DPA in German 1422 GMT 31 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3103151194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn -- FRG Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel has 
called the cease-fire in Krajina and the founding of a 
federation between the Bosnian Muslims and Croats "encouraging 
steps on the path toward a comprehensive peace settlement for 
the entire former Yugoslavia." In a statement disseminated in 
Bonn on Thursday [31 March], Kinkel stressed that "this positive 
development must now be used" to come "to a peaceful solution of 
all pending problems." At the same time, the minister stressed 
the human rights violations in the parts of Bosnia that are 
controlled by the Serbs musts come to an end. 

</TEXT>

