<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Prevent Superhighway Blockade by Kurds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Prevent Superhighway Blockade by Kurds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3103190894 Hamburg DPA in German 1751 GMT 31 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3103190894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Goettingen (DPA) -- On Thursday afternoon [31 
March] about 150 members and sympathizers of the Goettingen 
"Solidarity Alliance for Kurdistan" tried in vain to block the 
Superhighway A 7 near Goettingen with bicycles. Police closed 
off the access points to the superhighway. 
  According to the police, among the demonstrators there were 
numerous autonomous persons, but only very few of the about 400 
Kurds living in Goettingen. Three Germans were temporarily 
detained. The action was to be aimed against German arms 
supplies to Turkey and the threatened deportation of Kurds. 
  Having played cat and mouse with the police for several 
hours, the demonstrators ended their attempts to get to the 
superhighway via industrial roads and slopes with a protest 
demonstration in front of the headquarters of the police task 
force in the evening. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

