<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Landshut, Germany, March 31 (AFP) -- Numerous 
Germans have lodged complaints of an inflammatory statement by 
the leader of the extreme right-wing Republikaner party, Franz 
Schoenhuber, the Landshut prosecutor's office said Thursday [31 
March]. 
  A senior official said they had received complaints from 
outraged private citizens "by the pound" and expected to receive 
more, after Schoenhuber's remarks about the president of the 
Council of Jews in Germany, Ignatz Bubis. 
  He said prosecutors were studying the possibility of legal 
action against the former Waffen-SS officer and member of the 
European Parliament, who Saturday accused Bubis of being "the 
worst inciter of race hatrid in Germany." [passage omitted] 

