<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The long-awaited meeting between Forza Italia and 
Northern League delegations is reportedly under way at an 
undisclosed location. Berlusconi and Bossi are expected to come 
to an informal agreement over the formation of the next 
government. This will not be easy because Bossi has already said 
that he wants a Northern League politician [Roberto Maroni] to 
be prime minister, while Berlusconi is himself bidding for the 
job. 
  Berlusconi's spokesperson reports that the meeting is 
proceeding well, while Maroni has said that a joint communique 
will be issued at the end of the talks. 

</TEXT>

