<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fishing Minister on Extension of Algeria's Waters </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fishing Minister on Extension of Algeria's Waters </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3003192194 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1600 GMT 
30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3003192194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Algerian Government has decided to extend its 
territorial waters. According to a draft decree-law, they will 
be extended 30 miles to the east, toward the Italian coastline 
and 53 miles -- that is nearly 100 kilometers -- to the west, 
toward the Spanish coast. 
  Fisheries Minister Vicente Albero underlined that Algeria is 
sovereign in its decision to extend its territorial waters. 
According to Albero, in order to continue fishing, one will have 
to sign fishing agreements with Algeria and create joint 
ventures with capital from Algeria and from a Community country. 

</TEXT>

