  [Text] In Washington, Spanish Foreign Minister Javier 
Solana, who met the U.S. secretary of state, has commented on 
the ongoing situation in Algeria and more specifically on the 
crowds of Algerians requesting entry visas to our country at the 
Spanish consulate over the last few days. 
  [Begin Solana recording] If there are massive immigration 
movements -- massive waves -- we will have to consider the 
