<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   ANAP Claims Justice Minister Responsible </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ANAP Claims Justice Minister Responsible </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3103194794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3103194794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Eyup Asik, Motherland Party [ANAP] whip, said 
that the tricks and fraud involved in the local elections of 
last Sunday [27 March] had not been seen in any elections since 
1950, and that the justice minister is mainly responsible for 
this. 
  At a news conference in parliament, Asik charged that just 
before the election schedule was announced, the justice minister 
replaced the leaders of the Justice Committees in 49 provinces. 
The Justice Committees appoint election officials. 
  Asik pointed out that in all the places where there was 
fraud, the Social Democratic Populist Party and the Prosperity 
Party contested the positions. The great majority of the votes 
found in garbage dumps, he charged, were votes for ANAP. 
  Asik stressed that the government parties lost close to 15 
percent of their vote. This shows that the people do not like 
the government policies, he said. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

