<H3> <TI>   Official Talks With Libya Held in Ankara </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Talks With Libya Held in Ankara </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3103113094 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3103113094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The official talks aimed at developing 
Turkish-Libyan relations were held in Ankara today. 
  'Umar al-Muntasir, Libyan secretary general of the People's 
Bureau for External Liaison and International Cooperation who 
arrived in Ankara on an official visit yesterday, called on 
Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin this morning. Later the Turkish 
and Libyan delegations headed by the two ministers met. In a 
statement issued prior to the meeting, Cetin said that bilateral 
relations were raised to their highest level through the support 
extended by Libya during the Cyprus Peace Operation and 
continued as a result of Turkey's contribution to Libya's 
development and advancement. He noted that the monies owed to 
Turkish contracting firms in Libya are being paid according to a 
system that uses oil as payment. Cetin added that all debts are 
expected to be paid within this year. Al-Muntasir stressed that 
Libya attaches great importance to its relations with Turkey and 
that it wants to cooperate in all fields. He will continue his 
contacts this afternoon as well and will leave the country on 2 
April. 

</TEXT>

