<H3> <TI>   Ciampi Meets Kohl for EU Enlargement Discussions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ciampi Meets Kohl for EU Enlargement Discussions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0104083894 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1603 GMT 31 
Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0104083894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Ciampi and Kohl Review European </F>
Union Enlargement, G-7"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, March 31 -- Italian Premier Carlo 
Azeglio Ciampi on Thursday [31 March] met in Bad Hofgastein, 
Austria, with German Chancellor Helmut Kohl for informal talks 
which focused on the enlargement of the European Union [EU] and 
participation of Russia in the summit of the West's Group of 
Seven (G-7) most industrialized countries, which Italy will host 
in Naples in July. 
  The premier's office here said that Ciampi had gone on an 
invitation from Kohl who is vacationing at the Austrian resort 
and would also review the results of the recent G-7 summit of 
finance ministers in Detroit, which focused on employment. 
  The talks on EU enlargement were expected to have dealt with 
the changes in voting procedure, especially veto powers, once 
Austria, Norway, Sweden and Finland join the European Union, 
January 1, 1994 if current time-tables are respected. 
  Both Ciampi and Kohl, the premier's office, share the view 
that the "concept of Europe" must be re-launched with steps made 
towards advancing European integration and in the fight against 
unemployment. 
  The G-7 summit will be held July 8-10. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

