<H3> <TI>   Investigation Into Possible Election Fraud Launched </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Investigation Into Possible Election Fraud Launched </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3103173994 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1450 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA3103173994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Mar. 31 (A.A.) -- Ankara Chief Prosecutor 
Nazmi Sarvan said today that his office took under protection 
ballots which were found in various places and launched a 
preliminary investigation. 
  As the fundamentalist Prosperity Party emerged as the victor 
of Sunday's [27 March] local elections, huge amounts of stamped 
ballots were found in various places, casting a shadow on the 
election results. 
  Sarvar told the Anatolian Agency that experts were to 
examine 
the authenticity of the ballots and will also receive the 
testimonies of officials who were on duty at the precincts 
during the election. 
  "The necessary announcement will be made at the end of the 
investigation," he said. 

</TEXT>

