<H3> <TI>   Rail Workers Urged To Protest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rail Workers Urged To Protest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3103134994 Paris AFP in English 1311 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU3103134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, March 31 (AFP) -- Rail workers in the CGT 
[General Confederation of Labor] labor confederation have called 
on employees of the national SNCF [French National Railroad 
Company] rail system to stage protest actions on April 7 to 
defend employment, the CGT Federation announced on Thursday [31 
March]. 
  It said the forms of the protests were to be discussed 
locally, but could include work stoppages. 
  Referring to protests by French young people against a 
government plan for low-wage youth employment, now dropped, the 
CGT communique said that "By acting to halt job cuts" at the 
SNCF and "in defending the future of rail facilities," the rail 
workers "are carrying on a struggle similar to the one waged by 
young people, who demand only the right to live and the right to 
stable and useful employment." 

</TEXT>

