<H3> <TI>   Reactor Explosion Injures 4; No Leak Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reactor Explosion Injures 4; No Leak Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3103180194 Paris AFP in English 1751 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU3103180194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Marseille, France, March 31 (AFP) -- An explosion 
Thursday [31 March] at a nuclear research center in southern 
France left four people injured but there was no radiation leak, 
officials said. 
  They said the explosion occurred in a building where an 
ageing experimental nuclear reactor was being taken apart. 
There was no danger of radioactive contamination, they added. 

</TEXT>

