BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed JWI: "European Union Calls On Turkey To </F>
Respect Human Rights"] 
  [Text] Brussels, 31 Mar (BELGA) -- Following the arrest 
last week in Turkey of six Turkish deputies of Kurdish origin 
and the lifting of their immunity, the European Union (EU) 
states, in a press release published in Brussels, "that the 
right to freely express your ideas is a fundamental liberty for 
all, a fortiori for members of Parliament." 
  The EU points out that "this right also forms the basis for 
parliamentary immnunity of representatives elected in democratic 
states." 
  More generally, the EU expresses in this text its "concern" 
at the worsening human rights situation in Turkey and states 
that "the fight against terrorism must be conducted with full 
respect for the law and human rights." 
  The EU wants to renew its "appeal in favor of a political 
solution to the problems posed in south-east Turkey" and is 
earnestly requesting the Turkish Government "to honor its 
commitments regarding constitutional reforms in the field of 
human rights." 

</TEXT>

