<H3> <TI>   Claes Supports Romanian Efforts for Integration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Claes Supports Romanian Efforts for Integration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0404094294 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 0855 GMT 4 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0404094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 4/4/1994 -- "Belgium supports 
Romanian efforts to integrate within European structures and on 
the other hand appreciates especially the constructive attitude 
of Romania towards the pact of stability in Europe in the 
prospect of the Paris conference of 26-27 May," (the official 
launching of that initiative) stated to a Romanian press 
correspondent in Brussels the Belgian deputy premier and foreign 
minister Willy Claes. 
  In a statement made after his departure to Sofia and 
Bucharest where he is expected to pay formal visits over 6-9 
April, the Brussels head of diplomacy stressed that "Belgium 
follows attentively the process of reform and privatisation in 
Romania." 
  In a gesture "with a symbol value for the joint cultural 
values of our united Europe" and as an undeniable illustration 
of the special friendly character of the visit, Willy Claes, who 
is also a talented musician, will conduct a concert of the 
Romanian radio symphonic orchestra. 
  Belgian and Romanian sources in Brussels are noting among 
other things "the double character of the visit, the bilateral 
and the European one," as well as its "considerable" duration, 
taking into account the busy schedule of the Belgian deputy 
premier who is also the acting president of the Ministerial 
Committee of the Council of Europe. 
  According to the same sources, Belgium "is aware of the 
economic and social difficulties implied by the Romanian 
transition, but it is determined to reassert -- through its head 
of diplomacy -- its support, as to its possibilities, for a 
democratic and European Romania." 

</TEXT>

