</HEADER>

<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Italy &amp; Vatican City </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi: `Differences Will Be Many, Profound' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berlusconi: `Differences Will Be Many, Profound' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0104132994 Milan CORRIERE DELLA SERA in Italian 1 Apr 94 p 
2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0104132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Milan CORRIERE DELLA SERA </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Forza Italia leader Silvio Berlusconi by </F>
Maria Latella in Rome on 31 March: "Berlusconi: There Are Still 
Matters To Discuss"] 
  [Excerpt] Rome -- [Passage omitted] [Latella] Mr. 
Berlusconi, have all the problems with [Northern League 
Secretary] Umberto Bossi and the League really been resolved? 
  [Berlusconi] No, no. We have a whole series of discussions 
and meetings planned. I am confident, as always, but there is a 
whole series of different issues that need to be discussed. 
  [Latella] Newspaper editorial offices are busy guessing 
about 
the composition of the government, rumors are circulating... 
According to the latest one, Ambassador Sergio Romano is to 
become foreign minister. 
  [Berlusconi] Well, I can tell you this: There has been no 
discussion about ministers with anyone. All the rumors that are 
circulating are without foundation. Nothing of what I have read 
corresponds in the slightest to the possible ministers suggested 
by the three leaders or, rather, by the three, four, or five 
leaders of the alliance. 
  [Latella] Is it possible to make a suggestion of how many 
ministries will go to the League? 
  [Berlusconi] The League will have its ministers, the 
National 
Alliance will have its ministers, and we will have our 
ministers, but they will all be people who do not feature among 
the names that have appeared in the newspapers. You see, we 
have not yet talked about individuals, because we are talking 
about substantive matters. I think this is the right time to 
discuss matters of substance; the names will come later. 
  [Latella] What will be the differences between the 
government 
that you intend to form and its predecessors? Is it true that 
you will reduce the number of ministries? 
  [Berlusconi] I have a very clear idea, and if I am to be 
prime minister, because there could be an "if," the differences 
will be many and profound. I have a clear program, but it is 
still to early to talk about that. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

