<H3> <TI>   Army Head Refuses Comment on Somali Criticism </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Head Refuses Comment on Somali Criticism </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0104123894 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1530 GMT 31 
Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0104123894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "No Comment From Chief of Staff on </F>
UN Report"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, March 31 -- Italy's army chief of staff 
Bonifazio Inciso di Camerana refused to comment, Thursday [31 
March], on unconfirmed reports from New York that the conduct of 
Italian troops in Somalia was criticised in a United Nations 
document. "This is a political problem," he said. "This is the 
responsibility of governments, they are international 
responsibilities.... We soldiers just do our job and carry out 
orders given to us by governments." 
  According to well-informed sources close to UN headquarters 
in New York, a top-secret document drawn up last November 
criticised the conduct of United States and Italian troops in 
the peace-making operation in Somalia, saying that they both 
acted on their own initiative, failing to take orders from the 
UN command. 
  The report is also said to demand that the United States pay 
reparations for loss of life during a campaign to capture 
warlord Mohamed Farah Aidid. 

</TEXT>

