<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi Comments on Milan Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berlusconi Comments on Milan Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0104132494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1241 GMT 
1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0104132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "The meeting was positive. We will form a 
government." This was said by Forza Italia leader Silvio 
Berlusconi at the end of the much-awaited meeting between Forza 
Italia and the Northern League. He is optimistic about how long 
it will take, but said that they had not yet discussed "the 
premiership or names of ministers." However, an agreement has 
been reached to reduce the number of ministries and 
undersecretaries. 
  The Northern League's Francesco Speroni pointed out that 
"the 
debate about the Constitution is continuing. We will meet again 
after Easter. National Alliance leader Gianfranco Fini can 
relax -- we will speak to him too." Umberto Bossi's candidate 
for the premiership, Roberto Maroni, reiterated that "federalism 
remains the most important point," while the Northern League's 
Gianfranco Fini played down Bossi's absence from the meeting. 

</TEXT>

