<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Comments on U.S. Envoy's Remarks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Comments on U.S. Envoy's Remarks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0204150094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1400 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0204150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis said the 
government understands U.S. coordinator Robert Lamb's latest 
efforts for an agreement on the confidence-building measures 
[CBM's] but it considers the results preordained because of the 
clearly negative position of the Turkish side. 
  Commenting on Lamb's statement that the process is 
continuing, Mr. Mikhailidhis also noted that he does not share 
the conclusions that portray the Americans as ignoring UN 
appraisals on the failure of the process. He added: The 
Americans know very well what is actually happening. The 
government is waiting for the UN secretary general's report 
while it completes plans for actions it will take after the 
report is submitted. 

</TEXT>

