<H3> <TI>   National Guard Adopts Additional Security Measures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Guard Adopts Additional Security Measures </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0204202294 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1900 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0204202294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Guard has adopted additional security 
measures along the confrontation line because of the continuing 
state of alert by the Turkish occupation troops and the 
pseudostate's forces. The National Guard has also made 
representations to the United Nations. 
  The aim of the Turks is to create a climate of tension 
following the deadlock in the proximity talks because of Rauf 
Denktas' intransigence. According to CyBC [Cyprus Broadcasting 
Corporation] information from military sources, the Turks have 
taken special measures of readiness in the Nicosia area and at 
points that they consider of vital importance, such as arms and 
ammunition warehouses and radar installations. The military 
personnel at guardposts along the confrontation line have been 
doubled. Senior officers of the occupation army carry out 
continuous patrols along the entire length of the Attila 
[Turkish troops] line. 
  Within the framework of measures adopted by the National 
Guard, strict orders have been given to the national guardsmen 
along the confrontation line to be particularly careful. 

</TEXT>

