<H3> <TI>   Libya's al-Muntasir Holds News Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Libya's al-Muntasir Holds News Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0104184094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1540 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0104184094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 1 (A.A) -- Turkey and Libya will sign 
a trade agreement on April 17, Libya's visiting Foreign Minister 
'Umar al-Muntasir said on Friday [1 April]. 
  Speaking at a press conference at the conclusion of his 
contacts in Ankara, he said that with the signature of this 
agreement a new phase will begin in trade relations between his 
country and Turkey. 
  He said the agreement foresees financing by Eximbank in 
Turkey and of a local bank in Libya. 
  Al-Muntasir said his contacts in Ankara were positive and 
constructive adding that new foundations were thus laid down for 
the strengthening of present relations, adding that besides 
bilateral relations, regional and international issues were also 
taken up with emphasis on developments in the Mediterranean 
region. 
  Al-Muntasir further said during his talks with Foreign 
Minister Hikmet Cetin and the latter assured him of Turkey's 
assistance for efforts to lift a UN imposed embargo towards his 
country. 
  Commenting on the Cyprus issue, he said that his country 
favours a solution that would be peaceful and acceptable to both 
sides, and which would not favour any of the communities on the 
island, treating them as equals. 

</TEXT>

