<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Cypriots `Determined To Further Relations' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0304051694 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0304051694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Hakki Atun, the prime minister of the Turkish 
Republic of Northern Cyprus [TRNC], has stated that they are 
determined to further relations with Turkey. 
  Atun and a delegation of Turkish Cypriot young businessmen 
participated at a meeting organized by the Aegean Young 
Businessmen Association in Izmir. At the meeting, Atun said 
that they are aiming at economic integration between Turkey and 
the TRNC. Pointing out to the importance of the political 
dimension in the economic relations between Turkey and the TRNC, 
Atun indicated that economic strengthening will give them more 
power at the negotiating table. 
  Answering reporters' questions, Atun said that the Greek 
Cypriot administration entering the European Union will 
undermine the efforts toward a Cyprus solution and will create 
great political drawbacks which will harm the Cyprus issue. 
  Later, the TRNC Young Businessmen Association and the Aegean 
Young Businessmen Association signed a joint declaration. 

</TEXT>

