<F P=102>   TA0204152594 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1500 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0204152594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Istanbul, April 2 (A.A) -- A Spanish tourist died 
of his injuries in hospital on Saturday [2 April] following the 
explosion of a time bomb planted in front of Kapalicarsi 
(Covered Bazaar) earlier in the day, officials said. 
  A Tunisian woman had also died in the same incident and 
twelve people are still under treatment in various hospitals 
around the city. 
  A time bomb that was set off at 10.50 A.M. exploded in front 
of Kapalicarsi killing one and injuring thirteen people. 
  No one has so far claimed responsibility for the blast. 
  On March 24 a similar incident in Kapalicarsi's Yaglikcilar 
Street had left four wounded, including two Romanians, when a 
time bomb exploded in the ladies' toilets. 

</TEXT>

