<H3> <TI>   SDPP To Apply for Cancellation of Election Results </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SDPP To Apply for Cancellation of Election Results </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0104183694 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1415 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0104183694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 1 (A.A.) -- Social Democratic 
Populist Party (SHP) [SDPP] leader and deputy prime minister 
Murat Karayalcin said today that his party will apply to the 
High Election Board to void the results of the local elections. 
  Karayalcin told a press conference prior to his party's 
group 
meeting, which will decide on whether to continue the coalition 
government, that his party was receiving a great number of 
documents, complaints and evidence, showing that the elections 
were fraudulent. 
  Karayalcin advised the citizens, already perplexed by the 
overwhelming victory of the fundamentalist Prosperity Party 
(RP), not to be provoked. 
  "Turkey is a state of law and the warranty of our freedoms 
is 
the legislation, not the municipalities," he said. 
  Karayalcin went on to say that no one had the right to 
intervene into the way people dressed, to the length of dresses 
women wore. 
  Karayalcin stressed that the country definitely did not have 
a Moslem-secularist conflict. 

</TEXT>

