<H3> <TI>   Unemployment Down; Minister Sees `Turn of Tide' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Unemployment Down; Minister Sees `Turn of Tide' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0304164094 Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG in German 2 Apr 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> AU0304164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Numbers of Unemployed Down"] </F>
  [Excerpt] As a result of recent figures, Social Affairs 
Minister Josef Hesoun has spotted a turn of the tide on the 
labor market. 
  "Unemployment is decreasing significantly," Hesoun said. At 
the end of March, 228,865 people were registered as unemployed, 
thus 4.3 percent fewer than at the same time last year. Apart 
from the stimulation of the labor market through the spring 
season and the mild weather, there was also a stimulation of the 
economy, Hesoun noted. With an unemployment rate of 4.6 
percent, as calculated according to OECD methodology, Austria 
retains the third best international position. Only Luxembourg 
(2.7 percent) and Japan (2.7 percent) have more favorable rates. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

