<F P=101> Netherlands </F>
<H3> <TI>   Plane Crash Kills 3, Seriously Injures 13 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Plane Crash Kills 3, Seriously Injures 13 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0404181794 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 1730 GMT 
4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0404181794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hilversum Radio Netherlands </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Here in the Netherlands an aircraft belonging to the 
Dutch airline KLM has crashed while landing at Amsterdam's 
Schiphol airport. At least three of the 24 people on board have 
been killed; 13 others were seriously injured and eight people 
received slight injuries. 
  The aircraft, a Swedish-made Saab 340, had taken off from 
Schiphol bound for Cardiff in Wales. Shortly after departure, 
however, the pilot reported engine trouble and returned to the 
airport. While landing, the plane overshot the runway, crashed 
into a nearby field, and broke in two. Eyewitnesses report 
seeing an explosion but no fire. Air traffic to and from 
Schiphol was temporarily stopped after the accident. 

</TEXT>

