<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Discusses Turkish Statements on Patriarchate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Discusses Turkish Statements on Patriarchate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0404172394 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0404172394 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Commenting on the continuous provocative statements 
by Turkish officials, Government Spokesman Evangelos Venizelos 
stressed that the Turkish Government ought to know that for the 
Greeks of Istanbul, international law and the Lausanne Treaty 
remain valid. Regarding the Ecumenical Patriarchate, the 
spokesman added, tradition and international law remain in 
effect. The Greek Government deals with these issues calmly and 
does not fall for the artificial tension that the Turkish side 
cultivates. 
  The newly elected mayor of the Istanbul region of (Fatih), 
(Mehmet Ali Sakhilu), recently stated that he would enter the 
Patriarchate from the gate closed in 1821 following the hanging 
of Patriarch Grigorios V. 

</TEXT>

