<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Justice Minister Rejects Deportation of Kurds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Justice Minister Rejects Deportation of Kurds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0404182094 Mainz ZDF Television Network in German 1700 GMT 
4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0404182094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mainz ZDF Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bavarian plans to deport militant Kurds to Turkey 
are not supported by Federal Justice Minister 
Leutheusser-Schnarrenberger. As long as there is even the 
slightest danger that the affected people will be threatened by 
torture and death, they must not be deported, she stated in 
Bonn. The minister pointed out that many Kurds have been 
recognized as asylum-seekers, and that, within the framework of 
the negotiations on the asylum compromise, Turkey was regarded 
by all parties as an unsafe country of origin. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-18400 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu065_h_94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-065 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  5 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bavarian Minister Rejects Criticism </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bavarian Minister Rejects Criticism </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0504100294 Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network in German 0900 
GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0504100294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bavarian Interior Minister Beckstein has rejected 
criticism by Justice Minister Leutheusser-Schnarrenberger 
concerning the planned deportation of militant Kurds. In an 
interview with western German radio this morning, Beckstein 
accused the justice minister of a lack of legal knowledge, 
stressing that the existing laws cover his action. 
Leutheusser-Schnarrenberger criticized the fact that a simple 
statement by the Turkish ambassador on the security of deported 
Kurds should be sufficient. She rejected the deportations as 
long as it cannot be ruled out that those affected do not face 
torture or death in Turkey. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-18401 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu065_h_94007" </HT>


