<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "DVU Does Not Want To Run"] </F>
  [Text] The right-wing extremist German People's Union 
(DVU) of Munich publisher Gerhard Frey, 61, does not want to run 
on its own ticket in the European and Bundestag elections. When 
the DVU did not manage to get into the local parliament at the 
elections in Hamburg, it renounced participation in the Landtag 
elections in Lower Saxony. Now the party is calling for an 
"agreement" with the Republikaner. Republikaner Chairman Franz 
Schoenhuber, however, rejects any cooperation. 

</TEXT>

