<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Decides Not To Privatize Hervet Bank </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Decides Not To Privatize Hervet Bank </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0104172894 Paris AFP in English 1652 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0104172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, April 1 (AFP) -- The French government has 
decided not to privatize Hervet Bank "in the immediate future" 
because of its difficult financial situation, which led to a net 
loss of 1.2 billion francs (207 million dollars) in 1993, the 
Economics Ministry announced on Friday [1 April]. 
  It added that the state, which holds a 89.41 percent 
majority 
stake in Banque Hervet via Compagnie Financiere Hervet, will 
take part in putting the bank back on its feet by providing 750 
million francs in the form of stockholders' advances. 
  That amount will be added to the 150 million francs already 
paid in at the end of last year. 
  The government's goal is to get the bank back to 
profitability this year, the ministry said, "so as to prepare 
for privatization under the best possible conditions." 

</TEXT>

