  [Text] The Americans believe that there is a possibe 
compromise formula on access to the fenced area of Famagusta 
that will be handed over to the United Nations. The CyBC 
[Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation] correspondent in New York 
reports that the Americans are promoting a plan to provide safe 
access to the fenced area of Famagusta in exchange for the 
removal of the area north of Dhimokratias Avenue from the 
package of confidence-building measures or an amendment to the 
timeframe for return of the area. The CyBC correspondent also 
reports that it cannot be ruled out that the UN secretary 
general and the Security Council's five permanent members will 
invite President Glavkos Kliridhis and [Turkish Cypriot Leader] 
Rauf Denktas to New York. It is also not ruled out that 
President Kliridhis will go to the United States by the end of 
this week for consultations with the leadership of the U.S. 
State Department and the Security Council permanent members. 
[passage omitted] 

