  [Text] Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis has stated 
that any further discussion of the confidence-building measures 
[CBM's] is subject to the Turkish side accepting the two 
unofficial documents proffered by the United Nations. He added 
that the process for implementing the CBM's has been terminated 
due to the negative stance of the Turkish side. The UN 
secretary general's representatives, the spokesman said, 
submitted proposals that they considered to be fair and to meet 
the concerns of each side. The Greek Cypriot side, the 
spokesman continued, cooperated in full and reacted 
constructively, in contrast with the Turkish side. Kasoulidhis 
also stressed that no political advantage the Turkish side is 
trying to gain through the CBM's process can be accepted. 

