<H3> <TI>   UN Urged To Stop Greek Cypriot Actions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Urged To Stop Greek Cypriot Actions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0404132694 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1030 GMT 4 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0404132694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Atay Ahmet Rasit, minister of foreign affairs and 
defense, has urged the UN authorities to stop the Greek Cypriots 
from taking steps that will lead the negotiation process to a 
dead end. 
  In a written statement issued today, Rasit charged that the 
Greek Cypriot Administration first stepped up its arms buildup 
within the framework of the Turkish-Greek joint defense doctrine 
and increased its number of troops. Now, he added, the Greek 
Cypriots are amassing troops along the borders and reinforcing 
their positions. 
  Rasit stated that the Greek Cypriot Administration which is 
leading the negotiations to an impasse is trying to divert the 
world's attention by accusing the Turkish Cypriot side. The 
aim, Rasit said, is to get rid of the confidence-building 
measures which the Greek Cypriots claim are no longer 
meaningful, and to ensure that the UN Security Council passes a 
resolution accusing the Turkish Cypriot side. 
  The minister of foreign affairs and defense called on the UN 
authorities to hold discussions with the Greek Cypriot officials 
as soon as possible, to prevent the tension being deliberately 
escalated by the Greek Cypriots from causing a confrontation, at 
this critical stage of the proximity talks. 

</TEXT>

