BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Cypriot House of Representatives and the 
Greek Chamber of Deputies have established a mechanism for 
continuous exchange of information, coordination, and 
cooperation in all international bodies to which they both 
belong, as well as for international bodies in which only Greece 
participates. House of Representatives President Alexis Galanos 
announced this upon his return this evening from Athens, where 
he headed a multiparty parliamentary delegation. The president 
of the House of Representatives and the parliamentary delegation 
also had a meeting with Theodhoros Pangalos, Greek Alternate 
Foreign Minister. 
  Speaking after the meeting with Galanos, the Greek alternate 
foreign minister described the state of alert by the occupation 
forces and other Turkish actions as very impudent provocations. 
They think that they are powerful, Pangalos added, but this is 
not the first time someone has threatened Greece with his size 
and was later ridiculed. [passage omitted] 

