<H3> <TI>   Yilmaz Voices `Doubts' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yilmaz Voices `Doubts' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0404192294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0404192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpt] Motherland Party [ANAP] leader Mesut Yilmaz has 
said that he has serious doubts that the sacrifices involved in 
the economic stability program will be distributed justly or 
that the measures will be definitely implemented by the current 
government. 
  In a statement after the ANAP Chairmanship Council meeting, 
Yilmaz said that Turkey has needed a stability program since the 
end of 1991, but that a very important period of time was 
wasted. He pointed out that the necessity was felt more 
strongly at the end of 1992. He stressed that this issue was 
not considered even in the 1994 budget. Yilmaz maintained that 
the economic stability program was delayed as a result of 
coalition negotiations. 
  [Begin Yilmaz recording] Before everything else, a stability 
program needs a consensus that a program is necessary. There is 
a consensus in our public today that these measures are indeed 
necessary. However, we are concerned that an incomplete 
stability program might destroy this consensus. [end recording] 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

