<H3> <TI>   Demirel: NATO `Main Guarantee' for Security </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Demirel: NATO `Main Guarantee' for Security </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0404124494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 0700 
GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0404124494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over still of President Suleyman </F>
Demirel] 
  [Text] President Suleyman Demirel has stated that the 
consistent and determined policies of NATO since its 
establishment play an important role during the last years 
regarding the great, historical changes taking place in Europe. 
In a message he issued for the 45th anniversary of the NATO's 
establishment, Demirel stated that NATO is still the main 
guarantee regarding the security and defense of member countries. 
  Demirel pointed out that the historical developments of the 
last couple of years created an optimism within public opinion 
and international political circles that peace and stability 
would be achieved in a short time. However, Demirel added, not 
before long a sad and realistic picture replaced this optimistic 
mood. This sad and realistic picture was created by the threats 
to Europe and its environs. These threats included policies 
based on annexing territories, ethnic separatism, and clashes 
which emerged from minority issues. Demirel indicated that all 
the countries are in agreement that NATO, which took significant 
steps toward applying itself to these new conditions, will play 
an important role in establishing and perpetuating peace and 
stability. 
  Commenting on the NATO-Turkey relations in his message, 
Demirel said: Turkey's joining NATO in 1952 was an important 
step taken as part of Turkey's national foreign policy since its 
establishment. Within this understanding and awareness, Turkey 
has become a secure and trustworthy alliance fulfilling -- with 
great sacrifices -- the responsibilities stipulated by the 
alliance. Turkey always placed solidarity to the alliance in 
the foreground. Turkey will continue on the same understanding 
and approach. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

