<H3> <TI>   U.S. Cyprus Coordinator Begins Contacts in Ankara </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Cyprus Coordinator Begins Contacts in Ankara </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0404132794 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 0930 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0404132794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Ankara, April 4 (A.A) -- U.S. special envoy for 
Cyprus, Robert Lamb on Monday [4 April] started his contacts in 
Ankara after concluding talks in Lefkose [Nicosia] and Athens. 
  Speaking to reporters before his meeting on Monday morning 
with Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin, Lamb expressed hopes that 
talks will resume for finding a common ground for Cyprus talks. 
  Answering a reporter's question on the confidence-building 
measures he said the document is a "dynamic one" whose contents 
may change. He added that what matters is to keep the balance 
during the process. 
  The confidence-building measures of the United Nations 
involves the opening of the Lefkose Airport to international 
traffic and the inhabited Maras [Varosha] section to the UN 
monitoring. 
  UN-sponsored intercommunal talks on Cyprus were interrupted 
last July. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

