<H3> <TI>   Demirel Welcomes Albanian President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Demirel Welcomes Albanian President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0404163494 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1533 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0404163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 4 (A.A.) -- President Suleyman 
Demirel said on Monday [4 April] that Turkey was willing to 
improve relations with Albania in every field. 
  Demirel, speaking after Albanian President Sali Berisha's 
arrival ceremony at the Cankaya Palace said the visit will 
contribute to Turkish-Albanian relations. 
  Demirel said with this visit cultural and historical 
relations will be enhanced. 
  "Turkish and Albanian people share the same standard of 
judgment and these two people feel sincere love and respect for 
each other," Demirel said. 
  Demirel said the visit takes place at a time when important 
changes are taking place in the region, the Balkans and the 
Black Sea region. 
  "Regional and international problems will be discussed 
during 
the visit," he added. 
  Demirel said Turkey is doing its best to support Albania's 
transition to a free market economy. 
  Berisha recalled that Demirel supported the improvement of 
democracy in Albania. 
  Berisha also expressed his pleasure with the positive 
improvements in political, economic and military relations 
between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

