<H3> <TI>   Commission Expresses `Concern' Over Kantor Report </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commission Expresses `Concern' Over Kantor Report </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0504130694 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1144 GMT 5 
Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0504130694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "European Commission Concerned Over </F>
Kantor Report"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Brussels, April 5 -- The European Commission 
on Tuesday [5 April] expressed its concern over what it saw as 
threats of sanctions against the European Union [EU] implied in 
the report drawn up by United States trade representative Mickey 
Kantor on alleged trade obstacles and said it would reply 
point-by-point to the charges made against the European Union in 
its own report. 
  Speaking to the press here, an official spokesman for the 
European Union executive added how this year the report from the 
U.S. trade representative was much better than previous years in 
the sense that there was less criticism of the European Union 
and even recognition that many problems between the United 
States and the European Union had been resolved over the past 
months. This is also due to the end of the Uruguay Round 
negotiations to renew the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade 
(GATT) which governs world trade. 
  At the same time, the spokesman stressed how the European 
Commission remain concerned over the threats implied in the 
Kantor report, in particular those of sanctions in the field of 
public contracts and the safeguarding of intellectual property. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

