BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Malta/Italy: Scalfaro </F>
Congratulates Bonnici on Election"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, April 5 -- Italian Head of State Oscar 
Luigi Scalfaro has sent a message of congratulations to Ugo 
Mifsud Bonnici for his election as president of the Republic of 
Malta and stressed the historic ties of friendship between the 
two nations, a statement from the presidential Quirinale Palace 
said here Tuesday [5 April]. 
  "In the tradition of the ancient ties of friendship which, 
for geographic nearness, similar historic and cultural patrimony 
which have always united our two peoples" Scalfaro said in his 
message, "I remain convinced that in the future the excellent 
relations between Italy and Malta can continue to develop in all 
fields." 
  "I am comforted in this" the Italian president continued, 
"knowing your profound awareness of our culture and its 
constant, sincere attention towards developing cooperation 
between our two countries." 
  "In forwarding best wishes for your mandate and the 
well-being of the Maltese people" Scalfaro concluded, "please 
accept, Mr. president, my most heartfelt greetings." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

