<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Displeasure With Envoy to Bonn Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0504133794 Munich FOCUS in German 2 Apr 94 p 210 </F>
<F P=103> AU0504133794 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich FOCUS </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Ambassador on Call"] </F>
  [Text] French Ambassador Francois Scheer, 60, has 
overreached himself with his criticism of [German Foreign 
Minister Klaus] Kinkel, which he launched via the German press. 
"One more blunder and he will be gone," it was said in the 
French Foreign Ministry last week. 
  At home Scheer has been known for some time for his 
willfulness. However, so far French journalists have 
deliberately kept silent about his excesses. 
  "Something like the incident in Bonn is simply inconceivable 
among friends," it is being said at the Quai d'Orsay. 
  As an excuse, it was stated that Scheer, who comes from 
Strasbourg, formulated his criticism more strongly than intended 
because of his inadequate command of German. 

</TEXT>

