<H3> <TI>   UDF Chooses Candidate for European Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UDF Chooses Candidate for European Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504192394 Paris France-2 Television Network in French 
1800 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-2 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dominique Baudis is the candidate of the French 
Democratic Union [UDF] to lead the majority's European election 
list next June. Two men, Dominique Baudis and Jean-Francois 
Deniau, have been competing for the position. It is the mayor 
of Toulouse who has been chosen by the UDF to lead the 
majority's list. The Rally for the Republic [RPR] will 
undoubtedly agree. The RPR and UDF recently agreed to present a 
single list for the European elections. This single list will 
probably be led by Dominique Baudis. 

</TEXT>

