<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   }Bossi Responds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    }Bossi Responds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504184294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1748 GMT 
5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504184294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "This move is a little strange. I think that he has 
lost his nerve." This was the first reaction of Umberto Bossi, 
leader of the Northern League, to the decision of Silvio 
Berlusconi to suspend negotiations with the League. 
  People, Bossi continued, can see that Berlusconi has broken 
off talks because of the fact that he is the one who wants to 
take charge. In that case we have not made a mistake in 
understanding that with a virtual party [as received] we are 
marching toward an autocratic type of government. We must now 
safeguard democracy. His nerves have got to him because he is 
used to having everything his own way immediately. He now finds 
himself face to face with an entire people. This is a very 
powerful force." 

</TEXT>

