<H3> <TI>   Fini Backs Berlusconi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fini Backs Berlusconi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504183794 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1807 GMT 
5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The leader of the National Alliance, Gianfranco 
Fini, has said that he is satisfied with the decision of Silvio 
Berlusconi to break off talks with the Northern League: "Other 
than a four-sided agreement which comprises the Forza Italia, 
the Northern League, the National Alliance and the Christian 
Democrat Center party, said Fini, there is room for nothing but 
an election. The only other possibility is a government made up 
of the League, the Party of the Democratic Left and the Italian 
Popular Party. If we returned to the polls, not a single 
representative of the League would be elected to parliament". 
  Berlusconi is right when he says that he cannot take 
anymore, 
continued Fini. " How can one carry on negotiations with someone 
who goes back on what they said the day before". 

</TEXT>

